The input `orders` is a 2D integer array.
Each element `orders[i]` is an array of length 3, representing a batch of orders.
The first element of `orders[i]` is the price of the orders.
The second element of `orders[i]` is the amount of orders.
The third element of `orders[i]` is the order type, which is either 0 or 1.
The orders in `orders` are sorted in ascending order based on the price.
